statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from `packs` inner join `category_pack` as `cp` on `cp`.`pack_id` = `packs`.`id` inner join `categories` as `cat` on `cat`.`id` = `cp`.`category_id` where `cat`.`category` in ('Bread & pastries', 'Meals', 'Other')

select `packs`.`id`, `packs`.`title`, `packs`.`price`, `packs`.`sale_price`, `packs`.`picture`, `cat`.`category` from `packs` inner join `category_pack` as `cp` on `cp`.`pack_id` = `packs`.`id` inner join `categories` as `cat` on `cat`.`id` = `cp`.`category_id` where `cat`.`category` in ('Bread & pastries', 'Meals', 'Other') limit 9 offset 0
select COUNT(cp.pack_id) as total, `cat`.`category` from `category_pack` as `cp` inner join `categories` as `cat` on `cp`.`category_id` = `cat`.`id` group by `cat`.`category`
